The search logic will be as follows: 

When a user types of an input “XXX” of length “L”, the list of following items from the bank column in the IFSC Master to be displayed in order of appearance as mentioned.

•	First – All the items in the bank column of IFSC master which begin from XXX in alphabetical order.
•	Second – All the items in the bank column of IFSC master which have one character “C” before the input “XXX” in alphabetical order.
•	Third - All the items in the bank column of IFSC master which have two characters “CC” before the input “XXX” in alphabetical order.
•	Fourth - All the items in the bank column of IFSC master which have three characters “CCC” before the input “XXX” in alphabetical order.

And so on.

If the user input “XXX” of length “L” and no items are found, “Bank not found” appears in the list. 


When user presses on any of the bank in the list appeared, it should proceed the user to the payment screen of Quick Transfer (To be proceeded in user story J27_28_29_02_Quick_Transfer)

